Preheat your oven to 200°C and put two large #saucepans{} of water with @salt{1/4%tsp} in each
on to boil for the potatoes and broccoli. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into roughly 2cm chunks
(peel first if you prefer). Separate the @broccoli{1} into florets (like small trees). Halve
any large florets. Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces.

Pop the potatoes into one of the pans of boiling water and cook until you can easily slip a
knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan,
off the heat. Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{1%splash} and mash with a
#potato masher{} until smooth. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover with a #lid{}
to keep warm then set aside.

While the potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.
Season the @British pork loin steaks{2} with salt and pepper. Once hot, add the pork steaks
to the pan. Cook until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} on each side. Transfer to a #baking tray{}
and top with the @rosemary{1/2%sprig}. Cook on the top shelf of your oven until cooked
through, ~{6-8%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat. The pork is
cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Once cooked, transfer the pork to a #plate{} and
cover with another plate or foil to rest.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in your (now empty) frying pan on medium heat. Add
the shallot and stir until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the @cracked black pepper{1%tsp},
@chicken stock paste{10}, and @water for the sauce{100%ml}. Allow it to reduce until thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

While the sauce is reducing, add the broccoli to your second pan of boiling water. Cook until
tender, ~{4-5%minutes} - it should still have a bit of a bite. Once cooked, drain in the
colander.

Stir the @creme fraiche{75%g} into the peppercorn sauce then take off the heat - add a splash
of water if it's a bit thick. To serve, reheat the mash if necessary. Slice the pork steaks
into four, then serve on a helping of mash with the peppercorn sauce spooned over and the
broccoli alongside. Enjoy!